    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe docs for `vim.fs.dir` state that it should return one of the following strings\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/cf9b7a37cc3cf0ba934865626e1f392e956a59b1/runtime/doc/lua.txt#L2476-L2477\n\nHowever, when opening a network volume / network file system, it returns nil for every both files and directories. This is due `uv.scan_dir_next` being [used](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/cf9b7a37cc3cf0ba934865626e1f392e956a59b1/runtime/lua/vim/fs.lua#L184) which can returns type `nil`\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/cf9b7a37cc3cf0ba934865626e1f392e956a59b1/runtime/doc/luvref.txt#L3077\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. mount a network volume\n2. open nvim in this volume\n3. `:=vim.print(vim.fs.dir(vim.uv.cwd())())`\n\n**Expect** prints string `<filename>` and string `<type>`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n**Actual** prints string `<filename>`\n\nvim.print does not print nils\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.4\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 15.6.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nghostty 1.1.3\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbrew install neovim",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "We can either update the documentation to include `nil` or update the implementation to manually look up type if returned value is nil\n\n```lua\nt = t or (vim.uv.fs_stat(abspath) or {}).type\n```\n",
